trans-unit.source: Represents a collection of <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.ClientTarget"></xref> objects.
trans-unit.target: Representa uma coleção de <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.ClientTarget"> </xref> objetos.

trans-unit.source: This class cannot be inherited.
trans-unit.target: Esta classe não pode ser herdada.

trans-unit.source: The ClientTargetCollection type allows access to the <xref:System.Web.Configuration.ClientTarget> elements of the <xref:System.Web.Configuration.ClientTargetSection> section element collection.
trans-unit.target: O tipo de ClientTargetCollection permite o acesso ao <xref:System.Web.Configuration.ClientTarget>elementos do <xref:System.Web.Configuration.ClientTargetSection>recolha do elemento de secção.</xref:System.Web.Configuration.ClientTargetSection> </xref:System.Web.Configuration.ClientTarget>

trans-unit.source: It belongs to a group that includes <xref:System.Web.Configuration.ClientTarget> and <xref:System.Web.Configuration.ClientTargetSection>.
trans-unit.target: Pertence a um grupo que inclua <xref:System.Web.Configuration.ClientTarget>e <xref:System.Web.Configuration.ClientTargetSection>.</xref:System.Web.Configuration.ClientTargetSection> </xref:System.Web.Configuration.ClientTarget>

trans-unit.source: Initializes a new instance of the <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.ClientTargetCollection"></xref> class.
trans-unit.target: Inicializa uma nova instância do <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.ClientTargetCollection"> </xref> classe.

trans-unit.source: The ClientTargetCollection constructor is not intended to be used directly from your code.
trans-unit.target: O construtor de ClientTargetCollection não se destina a ser utilizado diretamente a partir do seu código.

trans-unit.source: It is called by the ASP.NET configuration system.
trans-unit.target: Denomina-se pelo sistema de configuração do ASP.NET.

trans-unit.source: You obtain an instance of the <xref:System.Web.Configuration.ClientTargetCollection> class by using the <xref:System.Web.Configuration.ClientTargetSection.ClientTargets%2A> property.
trans-unit.target: Obter uma instância do <xref:System.Web.Configuration.ClientTargetCollection>classe utilizando o <xref:System.Web.Configuration.ClientTargetSection.ClientTargets%2A>propriedade.</xref:System.Web.Configuration.ClientTargetSection.ClientTargets%2A> </xref:System.Web.Configuration.ClientTargetCollection>

trans-unit.source: Adds the specified <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.ClientTarget"></xref> object to the collection.
trans-unit.target: Adiciona especificado <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.ClientTarget"> </xref> objeto à coleção.

trans-unit.source: Before adding a client target to the collection, you must create a <xref:System.Web.Configuration.ClientTarget> object and initialize its <xref:System.Web.Configuration.ClientTarget.Alias%2A> and <xref:System.Web.Configuration.ClientTarget.UserAgent%2A> properties.
trans-unit.target: Antes de adicionar um destino de cliente para a coleção, tem de criar um <xref:System.Web.Configuration.ClientTarget>objeto e inicializar a respetiva <xref:System.Web.Configuration.ClientTarget.Alias%2A>e <xref:System.Web.Configuration.ClientTarget.UserAgent%2A>Propriedades.</xref:System.Web.Configuration.ClientTarget.UserAgent%2A> </xref:System.Web.Configuration.ClientTarget.Alias%2A> </xref:System.Web.Configuration.ClientTarget>

trans-unit.source: The <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.ClientTarget"></xref> to add to the collection.
trans-unit.target: O <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.ClientTarget"> </xref> para adicionar à coleção.

trans-unit.source: Returns an array of the keys for all the configuration elements contained in the <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.ClientTargetCollection"></xref> collection.
trans-unit.target: Devolve uma matriz das chaves para todos os elementos de configuração contidos o <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.ClientTargetCollection"> </xref> coleção.

trans-unit.source: The array of the keys for all of the <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.ClientTarget"></xref> objects contained in the <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.ClientTargetCollection"></xref>.
trans-unit.target: A matriz das chaves para todas as <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.ClientTarget"> </xref> objetos contidos no <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.ClientTargetCollection"> </xref>.

trans-unit.source: Removes all the <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.ClientTarget"></xref> objects from the collection.
trans-unit.target: Remove todas as <xref href="System.Web.Configuration.ClientTarget"> </xref> objetos da coleção.

trans-unit.source: The result of updating the configuration file after calling the Clear method is dependent upon the <xref:System.Configuration.ConfigurationSaveMode> value chosen.
trans-unit.target: O resultado de atualizar o ficheiro de configuração depois de chamar o método Clear está dependente do <xref:System.Configuration.ConfigurationSaveMode>valor escolhida.</xref:System.Configuration.ConfigurationSaveMode>

trans-unit.source: To update the configuration file you use one of these two methods: <xref:System.Configuration.Configuration.Save%2A?displayProperty=fullName> or <xref:System.Configuration.Configuration.Save%2A?displayProperty=fullName>.
trans-unit.target: Para atualizar o ficheiro de configuração utiliza um destes dois métodos: <xref:System.Configuration.Configuration.Save%2A?displayProperty=fullName>ou <xref:System.Configuration.Configuration.Save%2A?displayProperty=fullName>.</xref:System.Configuration.Configuration.Save%2A?displayProperty=fullName> </xref:System.Configuration.Configuration.Save%2A?displayProperty=fullName>

trans-unit.source: > [!NOTE] > Calling <xref:System.Configuration.Configuration.Save%2A?displayProperty=fullName> is equivalent to calling <xref:System.Configuration.Configuration.Save%2A> when the <xref:System.Configuration.ConfigurationSaveMode> value is modified.
trans-unit.target: > [!NOTE] > Chamar <xref:System.Configuration.Configuration.Save%2A?displayProperty=fullName>é equivalente a chamar <xref:System.Configuration.Configuration.Save%2A>quando o <xref:System.Configuration.ConfigurationSaveMode>valor é modificado.</xref:System.Configuration.ConfigurationSaveMode> </xref:System.Configuration.Configuration.Save%2A> </xref:System.Configuration.Configuration.Save%2A?displayProperty=fullName>

trans-unit.source: If you use the <xref:System.Configuration.Configuration.Save%2A?displayProperty=fullName> method, the following conditions apply: - If you pass the <xref:System.Configuration.ConfigurationSaveMode> or <xref:System.Configuration.ConfigurationSaveMode> parameter value, then a `clear` element is inserted into the `clientTarget` section of the configuration file at the current hierarchy level.
trans-unit.target: Se utilizar o <xref:System.Configuration.Configuration.Save%2A?displayProperty=fullName>aplicam do método, as seguintes condições: - se passa o <xref:System.Configuration.ConfigurationSaveMode>ou <xref:System.Configuration.ConfigurationSaveMode>valor do parâmetro, então, um `clear` elemento é inserido o `clientTarget` secção do ficheiro de configuração ao nível da hierarquia atual.</xref:System.Configuration.ConfigurationSaveMode> </xref:System.Configuration.ConfigurationSaveMode> </xref:System.Configuration.Configuration.Save%2A?displayProperty=fullName>

trans-unit.source: - If you pass the <xref:System.Configuration.ConfigurationSaveMode> parameter value, a series of `remove` elements are added to the `clientTarget` section of the configuration file at the current hierarchy level.
trans-unit.target: -Se passa o <xref:System.Configuration.ConfigurationSaveMode>valor do parâmetro, uma série de `remove` elementos são adicionados para o `clientTarget` secção do ficheiro de configuração ao nível da hierarquia atual.</xref:System.Configuration.ConfigurationSaveMode>

trans-unit.source: This removes all references to the `add` elements defined in the parent configuration files at higher levels in the hierarchy.
trans-unit.target: Esta ação remove todas as referências para o `add` elementos definidos nos ficheiros de configuração principal níveis superior na hierarquia.

trans-unit.source: With the <xref:System.Configuration.ConfigurationSaveMode> enumeration value, one additional property on the collection affects what gets serialized to the configuration file.
trans-unit.target: Com o <xref:System.Configuration.ConfigurationSaveMode>valor de enumeração, uma propriedade adicional na coleção de afeta o que obtém serializado para o ficheiro de configuração.</xref:System.Configuration.ConfigurationSaveMode>

trans-unit.source: The property is <xref:System.Configuration.ConfigurationElementCollection.EmitClear%2A> and is `false` by default.
trans-unit.target: A propriedade é <xref:System.Configuration.ConfigurationElementCollection.EmitClear%2A>e é `false` por predefinição.</xref:System.Configuration.ConfigurationElementCollection.EmitClear%2A>

trans-unit.source: One of the following conditions applies: - When <xref:System.Configuration.ConfigurationElementCollection.EmitClear%2A> is set to `true`, a `clear` element is inserted into the `clientTarget` section of the configuration file at the current hierarchy level.
trans-unit.target: Uma das seguintes condições aplicam-se: - quando <xref:System.Configuration.ConfigurationElementCollection.EmitClear%2A>está definido como `true`, um `clear` elemento é inserido o `clientTarget` secção do ficheiro de configuração ao nível da hierarquia atual.</xref:System.Configuration.ConfigurationElementCollection.EmitClear%2A>

trans-unit.source: This removes all references to the `add` elements defined in the parent configuration files at higher levels in the hierarchy.
trans-unit.target: Esta ação remove todas as referências para o `add` elementos definidos nos ficheiros de configuração principal níveis superior na hierarquia.

trans-unit.source: - When <xref:System.Configuration.ConfigurationElementCollection.EmitClear%2A> is set to `false`, the `clear` element is removed from the `clientTarget` section of the configuration file at the current hierarchy level, if it exists.
trans-unit.target: -Quando <xref:System.Configuration.ConfigurationElementCollection.EmitClear%2A>está definido como `false`, a `clear` elemento é removido do `clientTarget` secção do ficheiro de configuração ao nível de hierarquia atual, se existir.</xref:System.Configuration.ConfigurationElementCollection.EmitClear%2A>

trans-unit.source: The Clear method actually deletes the `add` elements defined in the `clientTarget` section of the configuration file at the current hierarchy level.
trans-unit.target: O método Clear, na verdade, elimina o `add` elementos definidos no `clientTarget` secção do ficheiro de configuração ao nível da hierarquia atual.

trans-unit.source: It also removes all references to the `add` elements defined in the parent configuration files at higher levels in the hierarchy.
trans-unit.target: Esta operação também remove todas as referências para o `add` elementos definidos nos ficheiros de configuração principal níveis superior na hierarquia.

trans-unit.source: > [!NOTE] > The `add` elements are not deleted from the `clientTarget` section of the parent configuration files.
trans-unit.target: > [!NOTE] > O `add` elementos não são eliminados do `clientTarget` secção dos ficheiros de configuração principal.
